Barcelona presidential candidate, Joan Laporta has said that Leo Messi will do everything in his power to remain at the Catalan club, as long as he receives an acceptable contract renewal offer. The Argentine superstar who has been the subject of transfer speculation and debate sees his current contract at Barcelona run out at the end of the season. Though Messi has assured fans no decision will be made until after the season. But despite the speculation and rumours, Laporta who is the overwhelming favourite to take over the reins of the Catalan club, after the resignation of Josep Bartomeu is adamant that Messi wants to remain at Barcelona. Laporta previously served as President of Barcelona from 2003-2010, where Messi made his Barca debut, and the club experienced unrivalled success both in Spain and in Europe. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-1525052 size-full" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/EoUwEVzUUAAigZB.jpg?resize=640%2C398&#038;ssl=1" alt="Messi will do everything in his power to stay at Barcelona ― Laporta" width="640" height="398" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/EoUwEVzUUAAigZB.jpg?w=958&amp;ssl=1 958w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/EoUwEVzUUAAigZB.jpg?resize=300%2C187&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/EoUwEVzUUAAigZB.jpg?resize=768%2C478&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/EoUwEVzUUAAigZB.jpg?resize=58%2C36&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/EoUwEVzUUAAigZB.jpg?resize=260%2C162&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/EoUwEVzUUAAigZB.jpg?resize=200%2C124&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/EoUwEVzUUAAigZB.jpg?resize=160%2C100&amp;ssl=1 160w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> He said: “Messi is now totally focused on catching Atletico Madrid in LaLiga and playing the Paris Saint-Germain tie in the Champions League,” Laporta is quoted by Sport. “I do not know if he will be playing on Sunday in the Supercopa de Espana final but he will be on the bench and it is important that Leo encourage his team-mates. “I see him more and more happy, he is enjoying it. I know that he wants to stay and I know that he will do everything in his power to stay as long as the club can offer him an offer that suits him.” Vanguard News Nigeria Barcelona announced on Friday that the club's presidential elections have been postponed after a rise in coronavirus cases prompted heavy restrictions in the region. The elections were set for January 24 but the Catalonian government told the club on Friday morning that exceptions to the rules would not be made… January 15, 2021 In "Sports" The future direction of European champions Barcelona will be decided on Saturday as almost 110,000 'socios' vote whether to retain confidence in incumbent Josep Maria Bartomeu or a previous president, Joan Laporta July 18, 2015 In "News" Lionel Messi and Barcelona could be heading for a sensational split, and the man who hopes to become president at Camp Nou next year admits: "It gives me nightmares." There are continuing doubts over Messi's interest in staying on at Camp Nou after a painful end to the season in… August 21, 2020 In "News"